---
title: "About"
---

Imani is a recent graduate of the Rollins School of Public Health at Emory University, where she earned her Master of Public Health with a certificate in Data Science. She also holds a Bachelor’s degree in Biochemistry. Her work sits at the intersection of data, health equity, and community impact.

Imani specializes in translating complex data into meaningful insights that support equitable health interventions. Her interests include sexual health access, forensic epidemiology, and structural racism as a public health crisis. 


